Name Rascal/Expressions/Values/List/Difference

Syntax Exp1 - Exp2
Types
Exp1 Exp2 Exp1 - Exp2
list[T1] list[T2] list[lub(T1,T2)]
list[T1] T2 list[lub(T1,T2)]
T1 list[T2] list[lub(T1,T2)]
Description If both Exp1 and Exp2 have a set as value, the result is the difference of these two list values. If one of Exp1 or Exp2 does not have a list as value, it is first converted to a list before the difference is computed.
Examples 
rascal>[1, 2, 3, 4] - [1, 2, 3];
list[int]: [4]
rascal>[1, 2, 3, 4] - [3];
list[int]: [1,2,4]
rascal>[1, 2, 3, 4] - 3;
list[int]: [1,2,4]
rascal>[1, 2, 3, 4] - [5, 6, 7];
list[int]: [1,2,3,4]
